{{Infobox figure skater |name= J. Lester Madden |image= |caption= |fullname= James Lester Madden |altname= |country= [[United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date|1909|12|13}} |birth_place= [[Boston, Massachusetts]] |hometown= |residence= |death_date= {{death date and age|1984|9|15|1909|12|13}} |death_place= [[Boston, Massachusetts]] |height= |partner= |formerpartner= [[Grace Madden]] |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[SC of Boston]] |retired= |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry| [[United States]]}} {{MedalSport | Men's [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze|[[1935 North American Figure Skating Championships|1935 Montreal]]|[[1935 North American Figure Skating Championships|Men's singles]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[1933 North American Figure Skating Championships|1933 New York]]|[[1933 North American Figure Skating Championships|Men's singles]]}} {{MedalSport | Pairs [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze|[[1937 North American Figure Skating Championships|1937 Boston]]|[[1937 North American Figure Skating Championships|Pairs]]}} }} '''James Lester Madden''' (December 13, 1909 &ndash; September 15, 1984) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]] who competed in [[single skating|men's singles]] and [[pair skating]]. His pairs partner was his sister, [[Grace Madden|Grace]]. He and Grace Madden were the 1934 [[United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national pairs champions]].
He was born and died in [[Boston, Massachusetts]].
In singles, he placed seventh at the [[1932 Winter Olympics]]. In pairs, he and Grace Madden placed 11th at the [[Figure skating at the 1936 Winter Olympics - Pairs|1936 Winter Olympics]].
